The ClassID trick is reminiscent of ObjC&#x27;s KVO addObserver:forKeyPath:options:context: - you typically pass a context to sort-out which type of object you are observing, because the observer only has one entry point for KVO notification.<p>static void* kFooContext= &kFooContext<p>...
[foo addObserver:self forKeyPath:@&quot;bar&quot; options:... context:kFooContext ]
...<p>if(context==kFooContext){
 NSFoo* foo=(NSFoo*)object;...
}<p>A better alternative is to use a blocks/lambda based approach, that way you can have several distinct callbacks and don&#x27;t have to handle routing yourself. (see Facebook KVOController)
